Feeding an obese child: do not take breakfast and take carcasses for dinner
More than one third of children aged 9 to 13 have overweight problems, 9% of schoolchildren have a weight above average and 5% are obese.
As the current research shows, obese children come from families with a malhealthy lifestyle.
This again shows how important the environment in which the human being and the models surrounding it are changing.
On the tables of obese children, for example, 50% carcass is more common than in children's families with normal weight.
19% of obesity had fries at dinner according to the survey conducted with an awareness action "Obesity is not a coincidence"
In the families of the small big sports is also not a habit, which is now the case for most today's schoolchildren - only 15% responded that at least once a week parents found time for active movement.
Survey of 900 children
The survey took place during the last school year and attended 900 students from Tsjechia primary schools.
It was the second edition of "Obesity is not a coincidence", action supported by the General Health Insurance and Unilever Society.
Since the beginning, more than 12,000 students from sixth to third have registered with this project.
One of the key factors that cause a dramatic increase in the number of overweight or even obese children is the absence of proper diet and insufficient physical exercise.
"Only half of the children questioned indicate, for example, eat 5 times a day breakfast-in case - lunch - taste-dining, which is a basic principle of good diet," says one of the results of the survey.
Without breakfast and carcass at dinner
The specialists draw attention to the fact that in order to have a healthy development, some basic details such as a family breakfast at the same time are needed.
In Czech Republic, only 23% of the families of students eat at the same time.
In most families each takes their breakfast alone.
And the worst thing that has been noted is that one tenth of the population does not at all take breakfast.
Breakfast is nevertheless the basis for a good daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that in families with obese children, ill-healthy fries are more often consumed.
Almost every student - without mentioning weight - drinks sweet drinks every day (70%).
More than 40% of the children in question regularly sports, but for parents it is half, only 15%.
Prepare your diet
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to prepare their own food on the basis of their own taste and personal opinion.
"The preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15 are far from ideal in terms of healthy diet."
Among their favorite dishes are many cakes, meat and sugarries.
"The most alarming is, inter alia, a great preference for sweet limonades," is indicated in the results of the survey.
For lunch it is the pasta that took first place right in front of white meat.
Children did not want fattening at all and the preference for fish and vegetable meals was very low.
Health cap
The survey also showed that children are ready to change their habits from the time they receive ad hoc information.
"In the course of a review of a group of survey participants who had completed the questionnaire after the awareness session "Obesity is not a coincidence", a determined willingness to move towards a healthy diet has been required," reports the results of the survey.
The most striking was, for example, with regard to sweet limonades as children started to give preference to drinking water.
Most often, children have cooked white meat and fish as the main dishes on the questionnaire and would reduce sweet dishes and "knedliky" (the Czech speciality of bread flour or potatoes).
