The basis for this long-term strategy was thrown by the first head of the company, the visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left this slogan that a large number of global problems can be solved as long as people are willing to think.
His slogan "PENSE!" has become the footprint around which the life of a future giant will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began to publish in 1935).
It was the basis of the company culture carefully developed by Watson.
For us IBM means a long-term thought of continuous movements directed towards the future.
IBM survived a hundred years because she remained faithful to her basic values and, however, did not be afraid to change everyone around her.
This has enabled us to transform technology, business and society during our first century.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more" has been the current director of the company Samuel J. Palmisano for the anniversary.
