Similarly, IBM has a well developed relationship system with the client.
The society was at the beginning great in discovering talents - as one of the first companies to have abolished any form of discrimination and could thus have the choice.
The current plan is entirely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy as it will be a woman- Virginia Rometty - who should replace Palmisano in the head of IBM.
It has been working with IBM for thirty years and is currently positioned as Chief of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM has been doing what is called jamy, brain-storming online over the last few years from which many future strategies and innovations are derived.
It is not surprising that there are many ideas - in the firm there are nearly 500000 people working.
An institution with a good name
