In addition, the total counting of votes received in all election urnes can be made if there is an indication that the difference between the alleged winner of the respective election and the second position in the election is equal or below a percentage point; provided that at the beginning of the session there is an express petition from the representative of the party and/or coalition that presented the second of the candidates reported.
The total ballot billing may also be made if, at the end of the joint billing, the difference between the alleged winning candidate and the second position is equal to or less than a percentage point, provided that there is an express petition from the representative of the political party of which the candidate was released second, in which the electoral packages which were subject to the partial billing will be excluded.
