Thus was the work of the person of Cali who identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A Cali dactyloscopist passed to history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials is crucial.
On 4 November, a Cali ITC dactyloscopist passed to history as the person who confirmed the identity of the Supreme Chief of the Farc: "Alfonso Cano", confronting his fingerprints.
Of the seven dactyloscopists working in the local offices of the ITC, this week it was the turn of "availability" of Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the field of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in the towns of Chocó, where many times he had to spend more than five days in the forest to arrive at the place where the bodies were to be identified.
In 2000, he was transferred to the capital of Valle and, following appropriate courses, specialized in dactyloscopy, which is the study of friction skin, i.e. palms and feet.
During the week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano Eliazar had been warned to take clothes with him for at least three days.
Something very big was waiting for him.
Friday night he went to Cauca in a Palmira helicopter.
He knew that he had to identify two bodies and that one of them was suspected of being the man who led the oldest guerrilla of the world, so he was asked to take the map with the ten fingerprints of Guillermo León Sáenz (his true name).
But when he arrived with the investigation team at the place of the body, he did not recognize it by his physical appearance, because it was very different from that he had seen in the media.
He had no beard, he was dressed like a peasant in the area, without glasses and much thinner.
But fingerprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a galtonian wolve, ink, a lever and a lantern, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the body with those of the card.
His eye didn't mislead him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was the responsible person who confirmed to the Minister of Defence, Juan Carlos Pinzón that yes, he was the chief leader of the Farc.
Looking for the fingerprint
For a dactyloscopist of Sijín de Cali, the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos made to Eliazar González in a press conference for the operation against "Cano" is very significant.
Many people don't know our job.
The dactyloscopy is an exact science, without a margin of error, which can be crucial in the resolution of crimes.
Apart from identifying the bodies, dactyloscopists support investigations for crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identity of the prisoners.
When captured, many offenders have false identity cards or have no documents.
We take their fingerprints and search them in the database.
The researcher noted that in a flight case he had to remove part of the wall from a house, because in this place the thief had pushed his hand to bring out a safe full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not adequate surfaces to draw a fingerprint from them, but in this case we have been able to get the fingerprint from the whole hand and identify the offender who had taken part in various flights," he recalls.
Fingerprints can also remove or confirm suspects in cases of homicide.
Recently we found a dead man with bottles of drink around him.
By termination of the investigation it was determined that a parent may be suspected of a crime and in fact a print on the bottle coincided.
Even if this does not guarantee that he is the killer, it places him on the scene of the crime.
An ITC dactyloscopist explained that "the fingerprints of objects with chemical or physical reagents" are extracted.
When they appear, a lifter or tape is used to remove them.
Subsequently, the prints are sent to Asif, the database of the declines, or to the National Civil Registry.
"The problem is that there are still many Colombians without papers," said the expert from the ITC.
He explained that everything is not how it is shown in the CSI television program.
As everything that shines is not gold, everything that you touch does not forcefully become a fingerprint.
However, it can be used if the necessary confrontation is achieved.
